Package: modelviz
Type: Package
Title: Publication-Ready Visualisation of Statistical Models and Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Pablo",
                  family = "Bernabeu",
                  email = "pcbernabeu@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A cohesive toolkit for creating publication-ready plots of
    statistical results and exploratory data summaries. It provides forest
    (coefficient) plots from fitted models or tidy estimate tables, side-by-side
    comparison of estimates from several models (for example frequentist and
    Bayesian fits, or the same model fitted by different optimisers), power
    analysis curves, regression-diagnostic panels, and a family of descriptive
    plots (distributions, correlation heatmaps, missing-data maps and scatter
    plots with fitted trends). A shared theme and helper functions give every
    plot a consistent look, and the package ships with reproducibly simulated
    datasets so that every example and vignette runs out of the box.
